Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel
and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.
Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave
to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{80%g} and pepper strips. Season with
@salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch} and fry, stirring occasionally, until
browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @Rogan Josh curry paste{50%g} and @white cumin seeds{1} to the pan.
Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @water{50%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{15%g}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly thickened,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Once thickened, add the @peas{120%g} and the cooked rice to the pan and gently mix
together until combined.

Cook, stirring, until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Stir through the @mango chutney{40%g} and season with salt and pepper.

Share the veggie pilaf between your #bowls{}.

Top with a dollop of @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and sprinkle over the
@toasted flaked almonds{15%g} to finish. Enjoy!